{
  "texts": [
    "Bias and stereotyping in LLMs, focused on specific demographic groups, have been an established research direction pre-ChatGPT (i.a.",
    "Caliskan, Bryson, and Narayanan 2017; Nadeem, Bethke, and Reddy 2021; Nangia et al. 2020; Blodgett et al. 2020).",
    "While papers accompanying the release of earlier LLMs such as GPT-3 (Brown et al. 2020), T0 (Sanh et al. 2022), Flan-T5 (Chung et al. 2024), or OPT (Zhang et al. 2022) still report scores on bias benchmarks, technical reports for more recently released LLMs seldom discuss bias mitigation during training or bias evaluation post training.",
    "Evaluation suites such as HELM (Liang et al. 2022), Eleuther's LM Evaluation Harness (Gao et al. 2021), Hug-gingFace's Open LLM Leaderboard (Beeching et al. 2023) also focus on explicit harms such as toxicity (Dhamala et al. 2021; Gehman et al. 2020), truthfulness (Lin, Hilton, and Evans 2022) and disinformation.",
    "HELM has only one bias benchmark for one task (Parrish et al. 2022)."
  ]
}